# Locked Palette v5 - NEVER DEVIATE

```css
--deep: #141a20;      /* darkest - base background */
--base: #2a3844;      /* dark slate */
--mid: #445868;       /* medium slate */
--light: #627888;     /* light slate */
--accent: #8498a6;    /* steel-teal accent */
--highlight: #a6b6c2; /* lightest - text, glows */
```

## NO INLINE STYLES

NEVER use inline styles. All styling must be in CSS classes using CSS custom properties.

BAD:
```typescript
element.style('fill', '#4ade80');
element.style('stroke', 'rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.5)');
```

GOOD:
```typescript
element.attr('class', 'line-measured');
```

```css
:global(.line-measured) {
  fill: none;
  stroke: var(--highlight);
  stroke-width: 3;
}
```

## BANNED COLORS

NEVER use:
- Neon colors (bright green #4ade80, bright blue #60a5fa, bright red #f87171)
- Pure saturated colors
- Colors outside the steel-teal range
- Vaporwave pink
- Corporate grey-blue
- Any hardcoded hex values in JavaScript/TypeScript

## Correct Usage

Use CSS custom properties:

```css
color: var(--highlight);
background: var(--accent);
border-color: var(--light);
```

For opacity variations, use rgba with palette values:

```css
fill: rgba(132, 152, 166, 0.2);  /* accent with alpha */
background: rgba(98, 120, 136, 0.15); /* light with alpha */
```
